about 1290","about 1350":"about 1350","1290":"1290","England":"England","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England","Askham, Westmoreland England":"Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Westmoreland","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lincolnshire): habitational name from the former region or county of Westmorland. The placename is recorded as <i>Westmoringa land</i><i>c.</i> 1150 and means ‘the land of the people living west of the moors’ (i.e. the Pennines), from Old English <i>west</i> ‘west, western’ + <i>mōr</i> ‘moor’ + the groupname suffix <i>-ingas</i> (genitive <i>-inga-</i>) + <i>land</i> ‘land’."],"variants":[{"name":"Westmorland","meanings":["English (northern): variant of   Westmoreland  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Gundreda de Westmoreland was born about 1265, in Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert de Sandford in 1285, in Askham, Westmorland, England. They were the parents of at least 4 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1265–":"umbes 1265–Surnud","1260–1356":"1260–1356","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1265–Female":"1265–Surnud","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1377":"1377","Abt 1265":"umbes 1265","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1260":"1260","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","about 1350":"umbes 1350","1290":"1290","England":"England","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England","Askham, Westmoreland England":"Askham, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1265–":"noin 1265–Kuollut","1260–1356":"1260–1356","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1265–Female":"1265–Kuollut","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1377":"1377","Abt 1265":"noin 1265","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1260":"1260","Abt 1290":"noin 1290","about 1350":"noin 1350","1290":"1290","England":"England","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England","Askham, Westmoreland England":"Askham, Westmorland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1265–":"environ 1265–Décédée","1260–1356":"1260–1356","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1265–Female":"1265–Décédée","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1377":"1377","Abt 1265":"environ 1265","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1260":"1260","Abt 1290":"environ 1290","about 1350":"environ 1350","1290":"1290","England